review_blob: Pale yellow. Unnoticeable aroma. Flavor falls in line with most pilsner kind of watered out and unremarkable and I still found a way to be displeased with the taste
Nice caramel malt aroma. Lighter amber color. Sweet malty flavor with enough hops to more than balance,
Amberish in color. Raspberry with slight hops in the aroma. The flavor kind of falls off the raspberry tastes artificial and sugar-candy like. The beer is lost.
Tap at Brewery. Dark amber in color. The aroma is sweet and almost carmely. The flavor is a nice balance of bitterness and fruity sweetness. Bitter finish approrate
Body light amber with okay head. Nose is sweet, caramel, hops. Taste hoppy, hammy, crisp. Nice texture. Warming finish. Enjoyable.
beer_name: Harpoon The Long Thaw White IPA

review_blob: Dark oragne, amber almost in color. The pumpkin in prominent in the aroma with recognizable spices. The flavor is the same, pumpkin, nutmeg, cinnamon but there is something else in there I cant figure out. Nice pumpkin beer. Certainly one the better ones in my opinion
Orange hue. Aroma of spiced pumpkin pie. Flavor follows suit decent pumpkin flavor with nice notes of nutmeg, cinnamon, and coriander. Real lively carbonation.
Never understood the popularity of it. Flavorful for a mass produced beer that you expect to be devoid of flavor anyways. But again just kind of unremarkable by those low standards
Orange/ yellow in color. Aroma is grainy malty. The taste is lighter than the aroma lets on, not a bland watered out beer just not complete i guess. Great marketing scheme though.

Pale pour. Unremarkable aroma. Flavor of slight carmel maybe, like its manufactures seem to do with most beers its kinda bland. I would rather order bud heavy than over pay for its twin in a pretty bottle

As the name imply pour brown. slightly thick foamy head. Nothing complex with the aroma. Flavor really nothing amazing either carmel, some roasty notes, I taste fruit sometimes but not in every sip. Kinda unremarkable really
Carmel color. Apple aroma. Not an overly sweet cider, not really a strong apple flavor really in my opinion just a quality cider.
As a red-headed Irishman I am obligated to love Guinness. The dark roasted flavor, creamy mouth feel, the characteristic head. I honestly feel closer to my Irish family with one in hand
Pale pour. Minimal yeasty aroma. Flavor is kinda water, bleak. Similar to most pale ales its a good drink from time to time but far from good
Amber with a thin head. Some caramel and maltiness fairly sweet. Decent drinking beer. Not as bad as many of the reviews
Bottle: Yellow-amber in color. Spicy citrus aroma. Taste is citrus, wheat malt...bright floral. A deliciously flavored and balanced IPA.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Sumpin Ale

review_blob: Draft at a college bar. Nice cider overall. Sweet apple aroma. Flavor is sweet but not overly sweet in my opinion. Nice casual drink
Yellow. Somewhat hoppy aroma, mild. The flavor is kind of watered out i feel but with some hoppy flavor in there. Finishes dry.
Standard yellow color. Minimal aroma that doest add much to the flavor. The flavor was pretty meek in my opinion. Somewhat boring even for a pale lager
Light yellow in color. Aroma of coriander and orange peel. Taste is the same. A nice refreshing summeresk beer meant to drink in the winter.
Beautiful beer reach deep color. Aroma is floral hops. Taste is indeed aggressive with a strong hop flavor throughout accented by small roasty notes
A nice clear gold color. Strong bitter aroma of hops and a little citrus. Flavor is robust with piney hops that ride all way through the finish. Great beer

Clear yellow almost light beer color. Aroma is sweet apple juice. The flavor as expected is a sweet apple juice but drier. Finishes nicer than most ciders I have had, a dry crisp finish, The mouth feel is somewhat different possible the carbonation. But one of the few sessionable ciders I have come across. The ABV can surprise you.

Light yellowish. Sweet sugary aroma. The taste is nice has all the lovable attributes of a hard apple cider but slightly sweeter and less tart to the finish. Very sweet not sessionable but a nicely put together cider

beer_brewer_name: Crispin Cider Company (Tenth and Blake Beer Co. - MillerCoors)
review_blob: Clear pale yellow. Aroma of apples. A dry slightly sweet apple juice flavor. Nothing amazing- light for a cider. Wont be your favorite or your least favorite cider

A red amber color with a big white head. Aroma was hoppy and fruity almost bigger than the taste. The flavor is hoppy but balanced out and tempered with some fruit notes, not as big as I was expecting but a very nice, drinkable, recommendable double IPA.

4 oz sample at the brewery. A yellow color with a standard white head. Aroma is spicy with pepper and clove. The flavor is fruity, sweet, kind of candy, the rye was there almost lost for me, its a unique flavor. I would like to try a larger sample before really bashing it.
Medium yellow color. Floral slightly hoppy aroma. Piney hoppy flavor throughout. Nice clean finish, Top notch pils
Straw yellow. Spicy and fruity aroma. Clove, honey, banana on the taste. Flavor dissipates quickly though. Light nice drink but not special either
Dark brown pour with a tan head. Smokey earthy aroma. Smokey, oaky, long flavor. Dry finish.

Deep yellow almost gold in color. The aroma is difficult to discern kind of a earthy hoppy aroma. Flavor starts hoppy but ends with a strong light roast malt flavor. Not every bitter but posses some complex flavors
Pours straw cooper. Citrusy grassy aroma with the discernible lager yeast in there. Taste is citrus and heavy pine bitterness.
Clear golden color. Citrusy malty aroma. Flavor is malty, grainy, floral and citrusy. Nice crisp easy drink, a favorite food pairing beer

Dark brown color with a creamy tan head. I didnt pick up much from the aroma but the flavor is robust roasted chocolate malt, touches of vanilla, milk chocolate, boozy but at 10-12% to be expected. Almost silky mouthfeel. Nice beer

Hazy yellow/ orange color with off-white head. Citrus and spices in the aroma. Taste is a mellow citrus with a well managed compliment of spicesprominently clove? Nice BBQ beer, wont blow your socks off though

Bottle: Dark amber color with a short lived cream color head. Aroma was promising with Christmas spices prominent. The spices are the carrier of the beer, nutmeg is prominent, with a little cinnamon. Not much else in there though kind of a spiced water with a background of earthy hops.kind of blah in my opnion
Clear amber color. Floral piney hop on the aroma. Biscuity sweetness is tempered with a persistent floral hop flavor. Finishes with dry crisp bitter finish.
Dark color with an light tan head. Nice hoppy aroma. Taste not as hoppy as expected but a good long-lasting bitter flavor throughout with a nice roasted malt balance. Enjoyable drink
Sweet cider. Tart apples, sugar. Not as hearty as other ciders. Nice casual not really sessionable in my opinion. Middle of the road cider

Difficult to find. Tired it on tap at the brewery and luckily college bar in Connecticut Looks just like great fruit juice. Didnt get the grapefruit from the aroma really but more just a sweetness really. Big grapefruit taste but nicely tempered. Very refreshing, perfect beach lounging beer.
Ruby color with foamy off white head. Piney, floral hoppy aroma. The long lasting flavor of piney fruity floral hops, notable crystal malt. Solid beer. Love the barrel series
Copper color. Light hoppy fruity aroma. Same for the flavor, maybe a note of carmel in there. Easy citrusy pale ale
Orange/gold color. Fruit aroma. Slight bitterness with a fruity sweet finish. Nice beer.
Dark Brown/black with beige head. Aroma of coffee, roasted malt, dark chocolate. Light bitter, milk chocolate, slight coffee, hints of vanilla. Very smooth, I dont drink coffee and love this beer
Amber with a nice head. Roasty aroma. Light roasty flavor with some light hops. Nice mouth feel. Easy relaxed beer
Tap: Dark amber/brown. Not much head to speak of. Flavor is unique kinda sour, sweet, with some roasty notes. Not off-putting just different

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Hazy yellow. Big lemon aroma. Nice light lemon taste with a mild finish. Guilty pleasure.
Dark brown. Mild roasty malt aroma. The taste is slightly sweet but the roasted malts keep is from being overly sweet. Light and sessionable

Tap: Moderate amber color with a small head. Smells of light caramel with earthy hops. The flavor is earthy caramel malty, would like to taste a little more bitter to pull the flavors together. Medium body moderate carbonation
beer_name: City Steam Naughty Nurse Amber Ale

review_blob: Bottle: Hazy yellow in color, nice head upon pour that dissipates to a think cover over the beer. Nice sweet fruity aroma. Flavor is heartier than the aroma lets on. Nice bitterness to start and ends in a fruity, grapefruit, apricot finish. Nice refreshing beer
